# Portfolio — core defaults

- **Package manager**: Use **yarn** only (`yarn install`, `yarn add`, `yarn <script>`). Do not use npm or pnpm unless the team explicitly migrates.
- **Framework**: **Next.js** (App Router) and **latest stable React**. Prefer Server Components by default; add `"use client"` only when needed (browser APIs, state, effects).
- **Local dev**: Run **installs, scripts, and servers through Docker Compose** (`docker compose up frontend`, `docker compose run --rm frontend yarn <script>`) so Node/yarn match CI/Vercel. Use host `yarn`/`node` only when Docker is unavailable. For **CV PDF** dumps, raster previews, and docx style extraction, use Docker only — see [`docs/agents/cv-pdf-docker.md`](docs/agents/cv-pdf-docker.md) and `sh scripts/cv/docker-dump.sh`.
- **CI**: **GitHub Actions** in `.github/workflows/` owns automated checks. Do not weaken checks to greenwash; fix or discuss.
- **Deploy**: Treat **Vercel** as the production target. Respect Vercel env vars and preview URLs; avoid hardcoding production domains in code.
- **Changes**: Keep diffs focused; do not refactor unrelated code. Preserve unrelated files and behavior unless the task requires otherwise.
- **Layout**: **Multi-package repo** (`file:` links) — **`apps/frontend`** (Next + **`lib/cv-pdf`** react-pdf), **`packages/storybook`** (DOM UI + Storybook), **`packages/resume-content`** (résumé data/types), **`apps/e2e`**, and **`tools/`** — **not** a monolith. Keep **separation**: app imports UI via **`@portfolio/storybook`** and composes **`@portfolio/resume-content`** into props; Storybook must **not** import **`@portfolio/resume-content`**; CV PDF code in the frontend imports **`@portfolio/resume-content`**; ESLint boundaries; CI splits per workflow (frontend vs Storybook vs resume-content vs e2e).
